Add Toast Notification Instead of Alert Boxes

ðŸ”§ Update index.html â€” Add this just before the </body> tag:

html

<div id="toast" class="toast"></div>

ðŸŽ¨ Update styles.css â€” Add this at the bottom:

css

.toast {
  position: fixed;
  bottom: 30px;
  left: 50%;
  transform: translateX(-50%);
  background-color: #333;
  color: #fff;
  padding: 12px 20px;
  border-radius: 6px;
  opacity: 0;
  pointer-events: none;
  transition: opacity 0.4s ease;
  font-size: 1rem;
  z-index: 9999;
}

.toast.show {
  opacity: 0.9;
  pointer-events: auto;
}

ðŸ§  In script.js, add this function:

js

function showToast(message) {
  const toast = document.getElementById('toast');
  toast.textContent = message;
  toast.classList.add('show');

  setTimeout(() => {
    toast.classList.remove('show');
  }, 3000);
}

ðŸ’¡ Replace alert boxes with toasts:
In the load logic:

js

showToast("Shot records successfully loaded.");
showTimestamp("Loaded");

In the save logic:

js

showToast("Shot records saved.");
showTimestamp("Saved");

In the load error handling:

js

showToast("Failed to load data.");

In the validation failure:

js

showToast("Invalid data format.");
